#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Durable live recheck for the coord feed plane (PR #4100's exit predicate).

The review team's standing critical on #4100: the exit predicate rested on
one-off transcript claims. THIS COMMAND is the durable recheck — anyone (or
any timer) can re-witness the predicate:

  uv run python scripts/hapax-coord-feeds-recheck [--json]

Checks, each named in the output, each FAIL carrying a next action:
  * units-tracked      — repo systemd/units/* byte-match the installed user
                         units (the tracked-vs-runtime inventory reconcile;
                         HAPAX_RECHECK_PREMERGE_BRIDGE=1 downgrades only
                         PR-bridge service ExecStart drift to WARN)
  * scripts-tracked    — repo producer/recheck scripts, helper scripts, and support modules
                         byte-match the copies under the activation root the
                         units ExecStart from
  * playwright-browser-staged — Chromium for the browser witness is pre-staged
                         under the governed source-activation area, not fetched
                         by this recheck and not borrowed from a host-local cache
  * units-active       — feed and coord rebuild timers enabled + active
  * coord-service-root — hapax-coord.service serves from the coord activation
                         worktree, not the mutable source checkout
  * coord-deploy-script — the rebuild target executes the tracked deploy helper
                         from the activation root and exposes its deploy contract
  * coord-deploy-exercise — the tracked deploy helper is exercised against a
                         temporary git origin/worktree with fake systemctl,
                         proving checkout, post-restart .deployed-sha,
                         idempotence, failed-restart retry, restart
  * feed-fresh:*       — every feed younger than 3x its timer cadence
  * vocab-parity       — observed stages map onto REAL ladder tokens (a token
                         outside SDLC_LADDER.stages counts as unknown);
                         unknown passthrough is honest -> WARN, not FAIL
  * coord-live         — /api/coord/version answers with a deployed sha
  * coord-provenance   — that sha matches the activation worktree's
                         .deployed-sha and git HEAD (deploy/rebuild provenance)
  * coord-boot-shell   — / serves the dark boot shell in <2s (pixel-level
                         instant-paint claims are witnessed by the playwright
                         harness; this is the HTTP half)
  * coord-last-good-paint — a browser witnesses #last-good-replay paint with
                         a dark surface and zero sampled white pixels in <2s
  * coord-yard-status-strip — a browser witnesses visible fresh (non-replay)
                         #yard-status health chips and the deployed SHA prefix
                         on the live page in <2s
  * coord-rails-consumed — /api/coord/rails reports feed_state=live with
                         stations from the CONSUMED vocabulary and item
                         stations matching the published event-log fold
  * coord-verdicts-visible — rails items match the exported review-receipts
                         dossier/acceptance feed (the "live BLOCK verdicts
                         visible" clause) and the browser DOM renders review
                         and receipt text

Exit 0 = predicate holds; exit 1 = named failures (warns alone don't fail).
Paths/URLs override via HAPAX_RECHECK_* env (the tests use this).
"""

